title: Job Fair of Chicago
description:
Wednesday, February 26, 2020
10:00AM - 1:00PM
University of Phoenix Chicago Campus
13th Floor, Suite 1300, 203 N. LaSalle Street 
Chicago, IL 60601
 
** Event Hosted at the University of Phoenix Campus for the GENERAL PUBLIC **
 
Pre-Register online at: 
https://catalystcareergroup.com/event/chicago-2-2020/

Plan to attend and meet face-to-face with several of the Chicago area’s finest employers. 

All of the companies at our job fairs have open positions they are seeking to fill.

Positions in the following areas are typically available:
Sales, Customer Service, Call Center, Management, General Business, Marketing, Retail, Administrative, Insurance, Banking, Engineering, Accounting, Finance, Education, Law Enforcement, Government, Military, Hospitality, Human Resources, Technicians, Telemarketing, Healthcare, IT, and more.

Tips for Success:
* Pre-register—Receive notifications of any updates or changes to the event, and receive information about upcoming events in your area.
* Dress professionally—First impressions go a long way.
* Bring multiple copies of your resume.
* Arrive anytime between 10 AM and 1 PM—Plan to spend 45 minutes to 1 hour at the event.
* Bring a friend—All job seekers are welcome.
* Prepare a brief but effective “brag” to let the people you meet with get to know you.
* Keep an open mind—Meet with as many of the companies as you can; you may be pleasantly surprised at what you find.

Remember, the best way to be considered for a position is to meet the hiring managers in person. Plan to attend this event!
 
Pre-Register online at: https://catalystcareergroup.com/event/chicago-2-2020/

title: "Sing! An Irish Christmas"
description:
Sing! An Irish Christmas: Keith & Kristyn Getty With Ricky Skaggs

Join Ireland’s own Keith & Kristyn Getty, known for modern hymns and carols such as “In Christ Alone,” for their ninth-annual tour of Sing! An Irish Christmas. Previously featured on public television to over 45 million US households and in the UK on BBC, this year’s concert has been reinvented around the ten most essential carols in history and will be broadcast internationally to millions of families on the Trinity Broadcast Network. The Gettys are joined by their band of virtuosic instrumentalists fusing Celtic, bluegrass, Americana, modern and classical music along with cultural Irish dance and the choral sounds of the holiday. Come sing along with Keith & Kristyn and special guest Ricky Skaggs for an evening that unites tradition and innovation in a vibrant celebration of the season!

title: Apollo Chorus of Chicago: Handel’s "Messiah"
description:
Apollo Chorus Sings Handel’s Sublime Messiah

For two performances only, this Holiday Season the Apollo Chorus of Chicago will perform one of Chicago’s greatest holiday traditions: Händel’s Messiah at the Harris Theater for Music and Dance, Chicago. Audiences flock to hear the thrilling renditions of Händel’s work as some by the Apollo Chorus. This year we’re proud to announce a quartet of internationally-acclaimed soloists, including soprano Amanda Majeski, mezzo-soprano Kayleigh Decker, tenor William Hite, and bass-baritone Darren Stokes.

title: Auditorium Theatre's 130th Birthday Celebration Open House
description: The National Historic Landmark theatre, which officially opened on December 9, 1889, has been a Chicago institution for 130 years. You’re invited to celebrate this milestone anniversary at a FREE Open House! Take a historic theatre tour, pose for a picture at a photo booth with an Auditorium Theatre-themed backdrop; sketch and take photos of the theatre; bring the kids for free popcorn and coloring; grab a drink at the bar; and enter a raffle for a chance to win free tickets to a future Auditorium Theatre performance. Photographs, program books, and posters from the theatre’s archives will also be on display.

title: Chicago Philharmonic presents Marcus Roberts Trio with Orchestra
description:
Chicago Philharmonic turns the heat all the way up with MARCUS ROBERTS TRIO joining the full orchestra onstage at Harris Theater on Sunday, December 8th. Witness the lightning-quick musical reflexes and creative imagination of international jazz superstars Marcus Roberts, Jason Marsalis, and Rodney Jordan as they bring Gershwin's sparkling Piano Concerto in F to life. Plus, the Philharmonic performs Duke Ellington's cheeky, jazzy take on the Nutcracker... wailing saxophones and all! 

Holidays: Marcus Roberts Trio + Orchestra
Sunday, December 8 / 3:00PM
Harris Theater for Music and Dance

Scott Speck conducts the Chicago Philharmonic
Featuring Marcus Roberts, Jason Marsalis, and Rodney Jordan

George Gershwin - Concerto in F
Duke Ellington/Billy Strayhorn - The Nutcracker Suite
Samuel Coleridge-Taylor - Christmas Overture
Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky - December from The Seasons

Tickets $25-$75 | Discounts for students and seniors

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

title: 2019 Grandparents Day at Chicago Toy & Game Fair
description:
EXPLORE, DISCOVER & EXPERIENCE!  
Join Us at North America’s Biggest Toy & Game Fair Open to Kids of All Ages! 
Grandparents Day Sunday November 24th! 
Children of all ages are invited to bring their grandparents to the Chicago Toy & Game Fair on Sunday, November 24th. Grandparents attending the Fair with their grandchildren will be welcomed into the Fair free of charge. Just register here and print out your ticket. Grandchildren will need to have a purchased ticket. 
What are you planning for the holidays? Come join us for a wonder-inspiring weekend at the 17th annual Fair brought to you as part of the Chicago Toy & Game (ChiTAG) Week - the largest toy and game fair open to the public in North America! Enjoy the many special events that appeal to all ages 0 to 100!
We showcase the best toys and games from around the globe. Build towers, play in tournaments, meet characters and more! The Chicago Toy & Game Fair is the destination to discover "what's hot for the holidays" and try out toys and games before you shop for Black Friday Specials throughout the holiday season. You are certain to find some great additions to your family collection of toys and games.
Highlights for 2019!  

Young Inventor Challenge
Frozen II Scavenger Hunt
Kids in Frozen costumes on Saturday FREE
Baby and Toddler PlaySpace
Blackhawks Inflatable Rink - Saturday Only
World's Largest Kid-Powered Rocket Debut!
WTTW Big Idea Traveling Lab Performance
Beer Garden with Popular Adult and Party Games
Meet Toy & Game Inventors from Around the World
Gator Golf Putting Station
Fuzzikins Decorate and Take
​My Buddy Wheels Riding Space 
Etch-a-Sketch with Princess-Etch
Photo Ops with  characters from Star Wars!
Shop for New and Classic Toys for the Holidays
Elan Dancers from Naperville Stage Performance
Yo-Yo Championship - Contestants from Coast to Coast
Interactive Exhibits, Test out Products Before They Hit Retail Shelves
Ben’s Giant Bubble Show, Giveaways, Stage Events, Magic Shows, Contests

Are you a Scout, firefighter, police, active military, educator or librarian? Check out our ticketing page for more information on qualifying for free admission. 
Parking and Directions: https://www.chitag.com/directions
Check out other events happening at ChiTAG Week:
Toy & Game Innovation Awards (TAGIEs) ($250)More details: http://www.chitag.com/tagies
Sponsored by:

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

title: Sequence Ch!cago
description:
Saturday, October 5 Kick-Off Concert: 5 – 8 p.m. South Dock MUSIC: DJ Shazam Bangles; Ana Ewerling; Brian Hoyt

Sequence Ch!cago returns to Navy Pier this fall and winter, highlighting the city’s vibrant arts and cultural scene over 10 dates throughout the season. Presented by the Paul M. Angell Family Foundation, the series includes performances from Chicago’s gifted musicians, handcrafted works by local artisans and special events, such as “Housegiving,” a house music celebration featuring a clothing drive for the homeless. The series kicks off on Saturday, October 5 and will conclude on Saturday, December 20 with “A Blues Christmas” in the spectacular Aon Grand Ballroom.

title: Columbia College Chicago’s Dance Presenting Series Presents  d. Sabela grimes  ELECTROGYNOUS
description:
Columbia College Chicago’s Dance Presenting Series Presents

d. Sabela grimes

ELECTROGYNOUS

“One of a mere handful of artists who makeup the vanguard of hip-hop fusion..”

-Los Angeles Times

d. Sabela grimes

ELECTROGYNOUS

*first time appearing in Chicago

Thursday-Saturday, October 10-12, 2019

7:30PM

Dance Center of Columbia College

1306 S Michigan Ave

*Post Performance Conversation: Thursday, October 10

a conversation immediately following the performance with the artists

“Black pain is very profitable in this country; we are focused on black joy.” -d. Sabela grimes

Keeping with this seasons idea of creating and fostering of connection through dance, the Presenting Series is excited to present d. Sabela grimes. After years as a company member with hip-hop pioneer Rennie Harris, grimes has developed a movement system derived from black vernacular social-dance practices, music, activism, and their interconnectedness. ELECTROGYNOUS imagines the inclusion of liberated Black bodies at the celebratory center of the work. Featuring video art by Meena Murugesan and digital illustration by Mr. Maxx Moses, ELECTROGYNOUS brings new speculative realities to the stage.

About the Dance Center: The Dance Center of Columbia College Chicago is the city’s leading presenter of contemporary dance, showcasing artists of regional, national and international significance. The Dance Center has been named “Chicago’s Best Dance Theatre” by Chicago magazine, “Best Dance Venue” by the Chicago Reader and Chicago’s top dance venue by Newcity, and Time Out Chicago cited it as “…consistently offering one of Chicago’s strongest lineups of contemporary and experimental touring dance companies.” The Dance Presenting Series recently celebrated 45 years of presenting contemporary dance in Chicago.

About d. Sabela grimes:

d. Sabela grimes, 2017 County of Los Angeles Performing Arts Fellow and 2014 United States Artists RockefellerFellow, is a trans-media storyteller, sonic ARKivist, movement composer cultivating a devoted interest in Afrobiquitous life practices. Sabela has conceived, written, scored, choreographed and produced several dancetheater works including BulletProof Deli, plus Philly XP, World War WhatEver, and 40 Acres & A Microchip:Salvation or Servitude from his EXPERIMENT EARTH sound-movement triptych. Recent creative projects include, ELECTROGYNOUS (2017) and Dark Matter Messages (2018). ELECTROGYNOUS is a dance theater experience which articulates that Black gender qualities are infinite, multidimensional and distinct manifestations of wombniversal consciousness. Moved by how Octavia E. Butler invents interrelated

notions of humanness+otherness in her Parable Series, Dark Matter Messages dreams Butler's unfinished manuscript, Parable of theTrickster, into an experience that realizes quantum Blackness as a means to play within the nowness of imminent futures. On faculty at USC’s Glorya Kaufman School of Dance, he continues to cultivate, Funkamental MediKinetics,a movement system he created that focuses on the methodical dance training and community building elements evident in Hip Hop, Black vernacular and Street dance forms. Sabela loves pancakes, speculative fiction and his kinfolk. dsabelagrimes.com

Funding Credit:

The Dance Center presentation of d. Sabela grimes is made possible by the New England Foundation for the Arts’ National Dance Project, with lead funding from the Doris Duke Charitable Foundation and The Andrew W. Mellon Foundation. Additional support is provided by the National Endowment for the Arts.

d. Sabela grimes / dsabelagrimes.com

title: THE MAKEUP SHOW CHICAGO
description:
The Makeup Show returns to Chicago!!  Experience the largest pro beauty event filled with top brands in Hair, Skin, Makeup as well as legendary makeup artists. Enjoy our educational opportunities on the Main, Seminar and Demo Stages, Hands-on Workshops & introducing our newly added Momentum Session Series.
Meet the CEOs & Executives behind the brands and stock up on all the essential products from large, indie, pro and prestige brands offering pro discount prices for your makeup kit and retail line up and watch demo and seminar stages.
Brand include: Smashbox Cosmetics. Perricone MD. Ardell Beauty. Temptu. Stila. Pacifica Beauty. Kryolan. Moira Cosmetics. Alcone. Crown Brush. Purlisse Beauty. Danessa Myricks Beauty. MUSE Beauty. Pro. Frends Beauty. Marmalade Nails. Glamcor. Pinnacle Cosmetics. Ruby May Cosmetics. Mario Badescu. and MORE! 

FAQs
Who can attend The Makeup Show?
Makeup Lovers, Makeup Artist, Retail/ Counter Artist & Specialist in Beauty, Cosmetologists, Nail Technicians, Estheticians, Hairstylists, Beauty/Fashion Students, Barbers, Fashion Stylist, Buyers, Beauty Executive, Product Developers, Photographers, Models, Aspiring Artist, Beauty Supply & Apothecary Owners & Employees, Salon and Spa Management and staff, Fashion and Costume Designers ,Wholesale & Distributers for Hair & Beauty Cosmetics , Actors, Dancers. and anyone else that love makeup as much as we do.
Note: 
One Day Tickets grant you entrance to The Makeup Show on either Saturday 5th or Sunday 6th. 
Two Days Tickets grant you entrance to The Makeup Show on both Saturday 5th or Sunday 6th.

Is there a minimum age requirements to enter the event?
No minimum age requirment however attendees must bring ID plus proof of credentials. 
What's included with your ticket?
Your ticket includes acces to pro discounts on the exhibitor floor, Main Floor Seminars, Demos and Main Stage Presentations.
Visit https://www.themakeupshow.com/chicago/ for further details on educational opportunity and Guest Speakers or email Sophia@themakeupshow.com to purchase Hands-On Workshops after ticket purchase. 
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
Yes, or show your ticket on your phone. 
I bought a Saturday Ticket but I can only attend Sunday or vice versa?
Your one day ticket grants you access to the show on either Saturday or Sunday. A two day ticket grants you access to the show on both days.
What are my transportation/parking options for getting to and from the event?
Please check out: https://www.themakeupshow.com/chicago/travel/
What's the refund policy? 
There are no refunds on tickets. 
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
email Joanni@themakeupshow.com or Sophia@themakeupshow.com. 
Please Visit https://www.themakeupshow.com/chicago/exhibitors/ for a full list of our Exhibitors, Special Guest Speakers, Education Opportunities and much more. See you at the Show!

title: Mission: Career Transition - Take Charge of Tomorrow with Career Ready Prep
description:
DeVry University will be hosting a seminar: 
 
Mission: Career TransitionTake Charge of Tomorrow with Career Ready Prep
 
At the event, DeVry University’s Career Services professionals will provide strategies on how to navigate a career fair, enhance your professional message and how to follow up after a career fair. Career Services professionals will also be available to answer any questions you might have about your job search.
 
Following the seminar, DeVry will be offering mints, hand sanitizer and seats to recharge at their booth at the DAV/RecruitMilitary Job Fair. Stop by to take advantage of this recharging station and ask any additional questions you may have about your job search.

title: Grand Cochon
description:
Sunday, September 15th from 6pm - 8:30pm (VIP starts at 5pm)
Tickets: General Admission, $150; VIP, $225

Grand Cochon, is the epic finale to the multi-city touring culinary competition. The winner will be crowned the "King or Queen of Pork" on Sunday evening, September 15th for the competition's 10th anniversary. Grand Cochon brings together the winning chefs of regional competitions - the outcome is a friendly competition featuring more than 2,500 pounds of heritage pork raised by American family farmers. The event will feature celebrated chefs and nose-to-tail cookery representing an array of cultures, cities and cooking styles. Each of the chefs is tasked with preparing the best 3 bites of heritage breed pig from the whole-animal menu they created to win their respective cities. The event is akin to a 40-course stand-up tasting menu, with dozens of competition plates served alongside artisan wines, boutique spirits, handcrafted cocktails, and some of the best cheeses, charcuterie, sweets, and pop-up food experiences the country has to offer. 

2019 competitors are: Bruno Davaillon, Buillon (Dallas); EJ Miller, International Smoke (Houston); Daniel Espinoza, Cantina Loredo (Chicago); Gabriel Erales, Comedor (Austin); Scott Hergott, Sky Bistro (Banff); Seung Joon Choi (NYC); Scott Pampuch, 4 Bells (Minneapolis); Jorgie Ramos, Barley (Miami); Brian Redzikowski, Kettner Exchange (Los Angeles). A portion of all sales will benefit Grand Cochon's sister charity Piggy Bank.

title: ALS Walk for Life
description:
Join the Les Turner ALS Foundation for the ALS Walk for Life on September 15, 2019, at Soldier Field. The 2-mile course winds along Chicago’s lakefront and through iconic Solider Field. Emceed by Phil Schwarz of ABC7 and Melissa McGurren of 101.9FM THE MIX, the event will include food, music, entertainment and children’s activities. 

Most participants walk as teams in honor of a loved one living with ALS or in memory of someone who has passed away from the disease. The event is a day of celebration, hope and courage with people walking for hope, walking for help and walking for life.  

With approximately 7,000 participants, the ALS Walk for Life is Chicagoland’s largest gathering of the ALS community. Registration is free, and participants are encouraged to fundraise for the Les Turner ALS Foundation. Parking is available in the Solider Field garages.

To register or learn more, visit www.alswalkforlife.org or contact the Les Turner ALS Foundation at 847-679-3311.

title: Cottonelle Superior Clean Country Fair
description:
In celebration of National Toilet Paper Day on Mon., Aug. 26, Chicago consumers will enjoy a peachy-clean experience unlike any other, brought to you by Cottonelle and Amazon’s Treasure Truck. Guests who roll on down to North Polk Park within Navy Pier will witness the “Cottonelle Superior Clean Country Fair” filled with a host of clean-themed activities, special guests and more! Activations include:

· Peachy Clean Finger Paint Art: Come leave your mark! Guests will be welcomed to show off their artistic finger painting skills and make their contribution to a number of 3D peach murals placed throughout the fair.

· Arcade Row: Classic arcade games with a peachy twist. Guests can practice their aim with Peach-A-Shot and Peach Bocce and then make their way over to the Prize Booth filled with Peachy Prizes.

· The Upgraded Bathroom Art Gallery: View a showcase of artwork by local artists Nate Baranowski and a selection of artists from Ava Grey Designs as they reinvent the porcelain throne. Guests of the fair are welcomed to admire the works of art and vote on their favorite masterpiece!

· The CleaningRipples Slide: Capture the thrill of sliding down a toilet paper-themed slide in your official Cottonelle Country Fair National Toilet Paper Day 2019 photo.

· How Do You Roll?: Join Cottonelle and influencers Timothy Delaghetto, Justin & Nick, Chantelle Paige-Mulligan, and Judy Travis in a nation-wide over/under poll and help finally answer the age-old question: What’s the proper way to place your toilet paper roll?

title: SPCS Young Professionals Conference: Chicago 2019
description:
We are excited to announce the 2nd Annual Young Professionals Networking Conference on Aug 23rd-25th, 2019 hosted in Downtown Chicago.
Registration is open through now through Aug 16th, 2019, please register. Space is limited!
The SPCS community is filled with knowledgeable, experienced, and driven members who can help young professionals reach their ambitious career goals. Through this networking conference, attendees will have the opportunity to build a robust professional network while also reinforcing the cultural connections that link us together.
Just as the SPCS Conventions have helped you meet new friends and connect with old, the SPCS Young Professionals Conference will help attendees meet new people to build their network in our community.
This conference will cater to those 21-35 years of age. Our goal is to create a strong professional and social network through the SPCS.
Location: Aloft Chicago Mag Mile
The registration fee is inclusive of:

2 night hotel stay at the Aloft hotel including taxes (not including incidentals) - Note: you will be paired with one other person randomly to room with unless otherwise specified during registration
Food for 3 day conference
Group activity on Saturday afternoon

If you have any questions, please contract us using the contact organizer form.
If you would to register without hotel room, please contact us using the contact organizer form.

Positions in the following areas are typically available:
Sales, Customer Service, Call Center, Management, General Business, Marketing, Retail, Administrative, Insurance, Banking, Engineering, Accounting, Finance, Education, Law Enforcement, Government, Military, Hospitality, Human Resources, Technicians, Telemarketing, Healthcare, IT, and more.
Tips for Success:
Pre-register—Receive notifications of any updates or changes to the event, and receive information about upcoming events in your area.
Dress professionally—First impressions go a long way.
Bring multiple copies of your resume.
Arrive any time between 10AM and 1PM—Plan to spend 45 minutes to 1 hour at the event.
Bring a friend—All job seekers are welcome.
Prepare a brief but effective “brag” to let the people you meet with get to know you.
Keep an open mind—Meet with as many of the companies as you can; you may be pleasantly surprised at what you find.


Remember, the best way to be considered for a position is to meet the hiring managers in person. Plan to attend this event!

title: VIP Seating for Chicago Immigrant Stories II: Finale
description:
In “Chicago Immigrant Stories”, CJP’s artistry of cross-genre collaborations melds with the musical culture of some of Chicago’s immigrant communities. The July performance is an orchestral culmination of a series of collaborations and workshops with musicians from Chicago’s Greek, Mexican, Bulgarian, and Argentinian communities.
Guest collaborators and featured artists include Grammy-nominated folk ensemble Sones de México; Greek saxophonist and composer Athanasios Zervas, and guitarist Petros Dragoumis; and resident CJP orchestra members - Argentinian pianist Leandro Lopez Varady and Bulgarian violinist Zara Zaharieva.

title: Yolanda Kondonassis performs Ginastera’s Harp Concerto with Grant Park Orchestra
description: Internationally acclaimed harpist Yolanda Kondonassis performs Alberto Ginastera’s Harp Concerto as soloist with the Grant Park Orchestra led by Emmanuel Villaume at Jay Pritzker Pavilion. Since its premiere in 1965, Ginastera's Harp Concerto has acquired an almost cult status as the definitive harp concerto of the 20th century. With its pulsing Latin rhythms, virtuosic displays, and creative use of many unique colors and special effects, the work has received numerous performances during the past several decades, nearly 200 of which have been performed by Yolanda Kondonassis. The program also includes Ravel’s charming Mother Goose Suite and Bizet’s First Symphony. This concert will be broadcast live on 98.7WFMT and streamed live at www.wfmt.com.

title: Hope for Healing Benefit Concert
description: 21+ / www.joesbar.comThe Social Alcohol Band has teamed up with Hope for Healing for a summer fundraising concert. Hope for Healing is an organization that focuses on supporting individuals and communities affected by addiction through education and harm reduction efforts. This charity was founded by the Stefani family following the overdose death of Matt Stefani. Matt was good friends with the members of The Social Alcohol Band and loved watching them play while in college. The Social Alcohol Band plays a wide array of different styles of music ranging from Tom Petty to Lou Bega, The Jackson 5 to Weezer, Billy Joel to The Strokes, Dave Mathews Band to Zac Brown Band, and everything in between. The ticket price includes a 3 hour open bar and a hell of a lot of fun!

title: WBEZ's Podcast Passport Presents Wow in the World Pop Up Party
description:
WBEZ's Podcast Passport presents Wow in the World Pop up Party live at the Chicago Theatre. Join Guy Raz, Mindy Thomas and The Pop Ups (three-time Grammy nominees and creators of the "Wow in the World" theme song) for a highly interactive show that engages curious kids and their grown-ups in science, wonder, imagination, and music and leaves them all saying "WOW"!

Wow in the World is a podcast for curious kids and their grown-ups that leads listeners on a journey away from their screens, inside their brain, out into space, and deep into the coolest new stories in science, technology, and innovation.

The Pop Ups is a collaboration, between Brooklyn musicians Jason Rabinowitz and Jacob Stein, which have set the standard for children's music since 2010. Their most recent album, Giants of Science, won their third GRAMMY Nomination for Best Children's Album, a Parent's Choice Gold Award, and had two #1 singles on Sirius XM Radio.

title: Socialism 2019
description:
No Borders, No Bosses, No Binaries
In a moment of rising class struggle, resurgent social movements, and the growing popular appeal of socialism, the Socialism 2019 Conference will be an important gathering space for today’s left.
We're excited to announce that this year the conference will be sponsored by Haymarket Books and Jacobin. We hope that the conference will continue to bring together hundreds of activists from across the country for four days of organizing, learning, and collaboration.
Featuring dozens of panels, lectures, meet-ups, and workshops on topics like the fight against racism, how to win gender justice, radical working-class struggle, current debates on the left, and more, the Socialism Conference is an important contribution to the new socialist moment.
For information on speakers, schedules, and logistics, visit the Socialism Conference website.

title: WBEZ Chicago Presents Seven Things I’ve Learned: An Evening with Ira Glass
description:
Ira Glass returns to Chicago for an emotional and thought-provoking presentation of his captivating stage show Seven Things I’ve Learned, sponsored by Barnes & Thornburg LLP. Using audio clips, music and video, Ira will share the personal stories of Americans from all walks of life and deliver a unique talk on the lessons he’s learned during his career as a storyteller.

Ira Glass is the host and creator of the public radio program This American Life, heard each week by over 2.2 million listeners on more than 500 public radio stations, with another 2.5 million downloading each podcast. He’s also one of the editors of the podcasts Serial and S-Town.

During this presentation, Ira will mix stories live onstage, showcasing his creative process for the audience. Audience members will learn what inspires him to create, what drives the work he does and how success and failure has impacted his career and life decisions.

title: TECHSPO Chicago 2019 Technology Expo (Internet ~ Mobile ~ AdTech ~ MarTech ~ SaaS)
description:
About TECHSPO Chicago 2019
WHERE BUSINESS, TECH AND INNOVATION COLLIDE IN CHICAGO!

TECHSPO Chicago is a 2-day technology expo taking place June 20 – 21, 2019 at the luxurious Hyatt Regency McCormick Place in Chicago, Illinois. TECHSPO Chicago brings together developers, brands, marketers, technology providers, designers, innovators and evangelists looking to set the pace in our advanced world of technology.
Exhibitors showcase the next generation of technology & innovation; including; Internet, Mobile, AdTech, MarTech & SaaS. Be prepared to be inspired, amazed and educated on how these evolving technologies will impact your business for the better.
As part of TECHSPO Chicago is a limited attendance paid event, DigiMarCon Midwest 2019 Digital Marketing Conference (https://digimarconmidwest.com). If the conference is where the learning, theory and inspiration happens, then the TECHSPO floor is where the testing, networking and product interaction takes place. 
Attendance is limited, Register today!

Venue
Hyatt Regency McCormick Place
2233 S Martin Luther King Dr, Chicago, IL 60616, United States



Step into the Hyatt Regency McCormick Place, where great things happen seamlessly. Conveniently connected to the McCormick Place Convention Center, this downtown Chicago hotel offers the ideal destination for you to work, relax and explore.  Enjoy the beautiful Lake Michigan backdrop and easy access to waterfront trails. Walk just outside of our doors to discover exciting Chicago attractions, like Soldier Field, Museum Campus, Millennium Park, and shopping on the Magnificent Mile. Hyatt Regency McCormick Place is a premier conference center venue where TECHSPO Chicago 2019 will be held.





TECHSPO Chicago 2019 will be held in the Regency Ballroom on the 2nd Floor.

title: Transport Chicago Conference 2019
description: Transport Chicago is an annual conference that provides a forum for the exchange of knowledge in transportation research, policies, and practice. The Conference, first held in 1986, explores a broad range of transportation modes and issues. This event regularly attracts over 300 academics and professionals from the Chicago region and beyond, offering an excellent opportunity for the transportation community to make connections and share experiences. Transport Chicago includes breakout learning sessions where attendees can learn about the latest trends, research, and emerging technology in the transportation field. Admission also includes continental breakfast, lunch, and snacks and refreshments at a networking session. Learn more at www.transportchicago.org or email registration@transportchicago.org

title: OUT OF SIGHT Chicago 2019 Orientation
description:
Thank you for joining in on a summer of self-discovery and empowerment through OUT OF SIGHT this Summer!
 
We look forward to working with you to create meaningful experiences for participants, across all ages and dedicated teen camps in neighborhoods throughout Chicago.


Last year, Chicago welcomed Lawrence Weiner’s OUT OF SIGHT, a participatory floor installation (modeled after a hopscotch) that invites active participation and encourages audiences to consider the direction of their lives. This project was inspired by the concepts: 
 
Exuberance   Energy   Happiness   Vision   Visualization   
Enlightenment   Spontaneity   Serendipity 

In 2019 large scale installations of the marelle (French for hopscotch) are open to the public at the following parks:

Eugene Field Park  (Albany Park)
Hamilton Park Cultural Center (Engelwood)
Julia de Burgos Park (Humboldt Park/Logan Square)
La Villita Park (Little Village/South Lawndale)
Maggie Daley Park (the Loop)
Ping Tom Memorial Park (Chinatown) 

We welcome you to participate in the OUT OF SIGHT Chicago 2019 Orientation as we build our summer together. You will have the opportunity to:


Meet the OUT OF SIGHT team and learn more about the vision
Park Supervisors discuss their communities and the teen camper interests
Teaching Artists sharing their talents and build out weekly activities
Motivational Edge Miami's founders speak about creating OUT OF SIGHT programming for youth

We are thrilled to have you joining in on this year of discovery and play. Please RSVP by this Saturday, June 8th.

title: Chicago Philharmonic & Cirque de la Symphonie
description:
Clowns, acrobats, contortionists and jugglers join the virtuosic musicians of the Chicago Philharmonic in an extraordinary spectacle for the eyes and ears at Harris Theater. Strongmen and aerialists perform superhuman feats onstage alongside the orchestra, perfectly choreographed to classic cinematic scores, in this spectacular family-friendly season finale. 

Cirque de la Symphonie is an exciting production designed to bring the magic of cirque to the music hall. For more than 10 years, it has thrilled veteran concert goers and new patrons as they see accomplished aerial flyers, acrobats, contortionists, dancers, jugglers, balancers, and strongmen perform to live symphony music. Classical masterpieces and film score favorites including selections from West Side Story, Superman, Star Wars, Harry Potter and more will dazzle audiences of all ages!

They will be joined by cast members from the Hamilton Chicago Company to perform a selection of songs from the Tony award-winning musical.

title: Bellavita Chicago 2019 - The Italian F&B Show | VIP Judge Pass
description:
Running for the fourth year in a row, Bellavita Expo takes place at the National Restaurant Association Show, Lakeside Center, May 18-21.
Visit Bellavita to discover a wide range of Italian food and beverages and apply here to vote for the best product of the show!
VIP Judges can decide to visit the Bellavita Italian pavilion on any day and at any time within the following judging opening times:


SATURDAY, MAY 18  from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.


SUNDAY, MAY 19  from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.


MONDAY, MAY 20  from 10:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m.



As a VIP Judge, you will get to taste authentic Italian delicacies, connect with a whole new group of suppliers, and award those exhibitors who have earned the top spot.
Did you know? Bellavita VIP Judges have priority seating for all the cooking demos, wine tastings and industry panels at the Bellavita Food & Wine Academy! Click here to see the full schedule.
Professionals eligible to attend the National Restaurant Association Show may obtain a Bellavita VIP Judge pass. We reserve the right to amend this list based on the criteria required to attend the trade show. Specifically, attendance will not be granted to anyone who does not clearly state their job role within the F&B industry.
All the F&B professionals who will make the selection process can get free entry for the 2019 National Restaurant Association Show upon request. The result of your application will be emailed to you before May 18.To learn more, contact Bellavita Awards Director Enrico Longobucco at elongobucco@quirismedia.com

title: Food for Thought: Connections Between Nutrition and Brain Health
description:
There is growing research evidence that what you eat can affect your mental health, including your mood and cognition. The evidence supporting nutrition’s role in brain health will be discussed in our next Science in the Parks program.
Specifically, Dr. Tussing-Humphreys will focus on discussing research tying a Western-type diet pattern to mental health disorders such as depression and dementia. She will also review how a plant-based diet like the Mediterranean diet can be beneficial to mood and cognitive health.  
Speaker:
Lisa Tussing-Humphreys, PhD

Dr. Tussing-Humphreys is Assistant Professor in the Division of Academic Internal Medicine and Geriatrics of the Department of Medicine in the University of Illinois at Chicago College of Medicine. She directs the UI Cancer Center's Diet and Behavior Shared Resource and is an associate in the UIC Building Interdisciplinary Research Careers in Women’s Health and an IHRP Fellow. Her current work focuses on obesity-associated iron metabolism dysfunction and its relationship to health status and disease risk.
A registered dietitian, Dr. Tussing-Humphreys earned her doctoral degree in human nutrition from the UIC College of Applied Health Sciences in 2009, writing her dissertation on hepcidin-mediated iron deficiency of obesity. She holds an MS in nutritional sciences from the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign and a BS in clinical dietetics from SUNY College at Buffalo. Before returning to UIC in 2012, Dr. Tussing-Humphreys was research scientist with the USDA Agricultural Research Service, and principal investigator of a church-based diet and physical activity intervention for African American adults in the Lower Mississippi Delta region.
Event Details:
Thursday, May 9th, 2019 from 6:00 pm to 7:30 pm, Ping Tom Memorial Park, Leonard M. Louie Fieldhouse, 1700 South Wentworth Avenue, Chicago, IL 60616.
This event is free to attend and seating will be first come, first served. 
This program is a part of the Science in the Parks and We Move Chicago initiatives.
  
 
Parking and Transportation:
Ping Tom Park is easily accessible by CTA Red Line Trains at the Cermak-Chinatown stop. For detailed travel information visit www.transitchicago.com or call the Travel Information Center at 1-888-YOUR-CTA or 1-888-CTA-TTY1 (TTY).

title: 17th Annual CHIRP Record Fair & Other Delights
description:
NOTE: WHILE ADVANCE SALES HAVE ENDED, TICKETS ARE AVAILABLE FOR CASH PURCHASE ON SITE.
It's the 17th year of the CHIRP Record Fair! Join us at Plumbers Hall to dig through thousands of crates of vinyl records, as well as DVDs, CDs, posters, and more. It's a music collector's paradise! We've got over 100 tables of vinyl this year - our biggest yet! And you can even get a sneak peek at the records we'll be slinging at the CHIRP records table, to prep for your early admission shopping!
In addition, our lower level will be filled with great food, beer, live music, and multiple Other Delights!

Gear Showcase on the lower level!
Kid's activities up in The Nest, with special programming from the Chicago Children's Museum!
Live music from OVEF OW, The Jellies, Baby Money (solo), DPCD, Thair, and Charming Hokum (Bob Gerics & Megan Donahue)!
Live music and comedy from Groovebox!
Special performances by the Blue Ribbon Glee Club and Reggio the Hoofer!
DJ sets from Van Paugam, Miss Alex White, DJ Chuck Wren, & Metro Chicago founder Joe Shanahan!
Food from Conscious Plates and Taco in a Bag - vegetarian options available!
Beer from Half Acre! Cider from Eris! Mezzo Spritz canned cocktails from Virtue! Wine provided by In Fine Spirits!
Coffee from Metropolis!
First 500 attendees get a free tote bag with download code for the CHIRP Record Fair Local Label Sampler!
Bike valet available, courtesy of West Town Bikes!

Early Admission ($25) begins at 8am and allows readmission all day long. General Admission ($8) begins at 10am. 
The CHIRP Record Fair & Other Delights is sponsored by Discogs!
The CHIRP Record Fair & Other Delights is a benefit for CHIRP Radio. Listen online at chirpradio.org or at 107.1FM on the north side of Chicago!
This year's poster (available through advanced ticket purchase for a discount!) was created by CHIRP's own Annabelle Goldin-Mertdogan!


FAQs
Will tickets be sold at the door?
Yes, though you should know - at-the-door sales are cash-only (ATMs on site), and the ticket lines are quite long in the morning. Buying an advanced ticket will let you beat the rush!
Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?
Nope! This is an all-ages event. However, we will be checking IDs for beer ticket sales and when said beer tickets are exchanged for drinks. Children under 12 are admitted free with a paying adult.
Are pets allowed?
No, no pets are allowed in Plumbers Hall.
What are my transport/parking options getting to the event?
The Plumbers Hall has a large parking lot surrounding the building, with plenty of spaces. We will also have a bike valet available for cyclists - courtesy of West Town Bikes!
From the Eisenhower (I-290), take exit 28B toward Paulina/Ashland. Head north on Paulina, turn right onto Ogden Ave, then right again onto Washington Blvd - we'll be on the left.
From the Kennedy (I-90/I-94 north of the Loop), take exit 50A toward Ogden Ave. Turn right onto Ogden and head south. Turn left onto Washington Blvd - we'll be on the left.
From the Stevenson (I-55), take exit 290 for Damen. Keep left at the fork to head north on S Damen Ave. After about 2 miles, turn right onto W Ogden Ave, then turn right onto Washington Blvd - we'll be on the left.
From the Dan Ryan (I-90/I-94 south of the Loop), head north past I-55 and exit onto I-290. After a mile, take exit 28B toward Paulina/Ashland. Turn right to head north on Ashland, turn right onto Ogden Ave, then right again onto Washington Blvd - we'll be on the left.
We are also located near the Ashland station on the Green & Pink 'L' lines, as well as the #9, #X9, and #20 buses. We are just over a mile west of the Ogilvie and Union Metra stations, and a little less than two miles east of the Western Ave Metra MD-N, MD-W, and NCS line station.
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
Nope! We'll be able to check you in with your digital ticket on your mobile device, or with your name. 
What is the refund policy?
All sales are final. If you cannot attend, a friend or family member may claim your ticket in your name on the day of the fair.
The name on the registration/ticket doesn't match the attendee. Is that okay?
Yes, as long as you can provide the name of the attendee that the ticket was purchased under.

title: VIVID 2019: A Celebration of Jazz
description:
VIVID 2019: A Celebration of Jazz

Tuesday, April 16 – 7:30 p.m.

Auditorium Theatre at Roosevelt University

50 E. Ida B. Wells Dr, Chicago, IL 60605

Free Performance

https://www.auditoriumtheatre.org/shows/vivid-2019/

 

Roosevelt University’s VIVID 2019 showcases performances by students and faculty (Victor Garcia, trumpet; Alejandro Cortés, piano; and Rubén Alvarez, percussion) from the Music Conservatory’s Jazz and Contemporary Music Program. CCPA Dean Emeritus Henry Fogel will be honored with the first CCPA Distinguished Achievement in the Arts Award. VIVID is a free event, but tickets are required. Tickets available to reserve through the Auditorium Theatre Box Office.

Celebrate National Beer Day in Chicago Style! State and Lake Chicago Tavern, theWit's award-winning eatery that takes traditional tavern dining to the next level, will be offering $10 Chicago Flights on Sunday, April 7th 2019 to celebrate National Beer Day!

While you're there, enjoy  State and Lake's sleek contemporary design that combines the flare of artisanal American cuisine with the warm welcoming vibes of your neighborhood pub. 

State and Lake is located at 201 N State St. and will be open on Sunday from 7am to 10pm.

title: 2019 Education Job Fair
description:
This job fair is being hosted by the consortium schools of University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC), Loyola University, and DePaul University. The fair will showcase employers representing private schools, public school districts, charter schools, and various non-profit organizations located throughout the city of Chicago, suburban locations, and other states (Wisconsin, Michigan, Colorado, Florida, and others).
Employers are seeking candidates who are education, social work, and other majors interested in working in education settings.
This Fair is open to the public and FREE! Bring plenty of resumes! 
DOWNLOAD THE 2019 EDUCATION FAIR GUIDE HERE.

title: Dan Navarro
description: With a career spanning decades Dan Navarro is perhaps best known as songwriter for artists as diverse as Jackson Browne, The Bangles, Keb’ Mo’ and Pat Benatar (the Grammy-nominated classic “We Belong”) to name a few. A multi-talented performer, Dan is a singer, a songwriter and a voice actor in major motion pictures, television series, & commercials. Having released a dozen albums – either solo and as Lowen&Navarro;, Dan Navarro released his first true studio-recorded solo album, "Shed My Skin" late last year and, as always, his songs are rich with insight and life experience, delivered straight-up, with honesty, grace and heart, in his moving and expressive baritone voice.

title: The Beach Chicago | January 19, 2019 – February 3, 2019 | Free Public Art Installation
description: Conceived by New York- based designers, Snarkitecture, The Beach Chicago is an immersive installation comprised of a tall enclosure which creates a large, open room filled with more than a million antimicrobial and recyclable plastic balls. Deck chairs, lifeguard chairs, umbrellas and signage mimic the sensation of a day at the beach, complete with a pier from which onlookers can watch and revel in the installation below. The Beach Chicago is presented by Navy Pier and Expo Chicago, and supported the Chicago Free For All Fund at the Chicago Community Trust, Hilton Worldwide and the Navy Pier Associate Board. Click here for more details.

title: Corey Smith Live at Joes on Weed St.
description: Corey Smith, the fan-made man, has sold over 1 million concert tickets, 1.5 million digital singles and over 220,000 albums.  Smith has amassed an unfailingly devout fan base, not only in his native Southeast region, but all around the nation, simply by telling it the way it is.  He has released 10 albums—including 2011’s Top 20 release The Broken Record.  Corey has written every word on every album himself and he produced 9 out of 10 of the records. In Summer 2015, Corey teamed up with producer Keith Stegall (Alan Jackson, Zac Brown Band) for his album, “While the Gettin’ Is Good,” which was released on Sugar Hill Records.  Smith’s concerts, which were documented on his last live record, Live in Chattanooga, regularly sell out, with audiences singing along to such fan favorites as the coming-of-age anthem “Twenty-One,” the nostalgic time warp “If I Could Do It Again” and the group hug “I Love Everyone.”   Corey consistently tours, hitting around 120 dates per year and has begun releasing singles from his upcoming project, the Great Wide Underground.

title: Kinky Boots
description: Inspired by true events, KINKY BOOTS takes you from a gentlemen’s shoe factory in Northampton to the glamorous catwalks of Milan. Charlie Price is struggling to live up to his father’s expectations and continue the family business of Price & Son. With the factory’s future hanging in the balance, help arrives in the unlikely but spectacular form of Lola, a fabulous performer in need of some sturdy new stilettos. KINKY BOOTS has won every major Best Musical Award and is represented around the world with the Tony® Award-winning Broadway company (now in its sixth year), an Olivier Award-winning production in London, and a production in Germany. Other previous productions include a past US National Tour that played more than 80 cities, an Award-winning extended run in Toronto, a production in Australia, two productions in Korea, and a Japanese language production.

description: Displayed on Navy Pier’s South Dock from December 7 through January 6, this captivating artwork by Serge Maheu uses light and sound to create twenty colorful circles that form a tunnel. As guests walk through, light and sound is activated creating a playful, multi-sensory experience.
